          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding: 0.75rem;"><strong>OAI</strong> (Official Action Indicated)</td>
            <td style="padding: 0.75rem;">~1.7%</td>
            <td style="padding: 0.75rem;">Serious — may trigger warning letter or further enforcement</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p style="max-width: 760px;">
      <strong>Translation:</strong> roughly 1 in 4 inspected US clinical sites receives actionable findings.
      Among the top-cited regulatory sections in recent warning letters: 21 CFR 312.60 (investigational plan adherence),
      21 CFR 312.20 (IND submission), 21 CFR 312.57 (record maintenance), and 21 CFR 50.25 (informed consent requirements)<sup><a href="#cite-5">5</a></sup>.
    </p>
  </section>

